        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T19:36:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s testing guarantees of UpdateSnapshot. I\u0027ve added commnets, see diff.\n\n\u003e in production UpdateSnapshot should be called in a retry loop\n\n1. RunInTransaction already retries by default on txn commit errors. Here goes your first level loop.\n2. CV code won\u0027t loop over UpdateSnapshot directly, as we don\u0027t expect high failure rate. And if we see high failure rate, it\u0027s either datastore outage OR we have too much contention on CL entity (\u003d\u003e design problem).\n3. But, the TQ task which polls Gerrit and does UpdateSnapshot (CL soon to come) is auto-retriable by Cloud TQ.",
      "parentUuid": "56adb039_5dd4a3f5",
      "revId": "642c96ae9e2d588fd6b44811990effcbfa143c44",
